Khan, now a UK citizen, allegedly drew a government salary from 2013-2017 while living abroad and acquired properties worth over Rs 30 crore.
title: ‘Drew salary while residing abroad’: UK-based Islamic preacher under ED lens; radical ideology charge

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Tech giants Microsoft and Google are reportedly threatening procurement executives with termination over failure to secure critical memory chip supplies from Samsung and SK Hynix. This intense pressure stems from the global memory shortage, driven by AI demand, leading to soaring RAM prices and forcing companies to restructure hiring for Asian supply chains.

description: India has introduced a new quality standard for incense sticks (agarbatti), banning harmful insecticidal chemicals and synthetic fragrance intermediates. Developed by BIS, this aims to ensure safer products, promote sustainability, and boost consumer confidence. The move supports the nation's significant agarbatti industry, a major employer, and enhances its global market access.

description: Aditya Dhar’s 'Dhurandhar' continues its historic box office dominance, crossing Rs. 634.3 crore by Day 22. Despite the Christmas holiday, Kartik Aaryan’s 'Tu Meri Main Tera Main Tera Tu Meri' struggled significantly, earning only Rs. 7.39 crore in two days due to limited screen allocation and the overwhelming popularity of the Ranveer Singh-starrer.

Investigations reveal a multi-crore racket involving diversion from legal channels, with kingpins orchestrating a complex smuggling network. Authorities are intensifying crackdowns, with multiple arrests and probes underway.

description: Dubai is embracing e-scooters for greener travel, but new RTA rules aim to boost safety. Riders must follow speed limits, wear helmets, and maintain distance from pedestrians. description: Rohit Sharma suffered a golden duck in the Vijay Hazare Trophy against Uttarakhand, while Virat Kohli impressed with a rapid 77 for Delhi against Gujarat. This contrast reflects their recent ODI performances, with Kohli in exceptional form and Rohit also maintaining strong scoring.

author: NEHA VASHIST
description: Filmmaker Madhur Bhandarkar shares his top cinematic picks for 2025. Aditya Dhar's 'Dhurandhar' starring Ranveer Singh and Akshaye Khanna leads the list. Bhandarkar praises Dhar's directorial vision and the performances of Singh and Khanna. 'Saiyaara' and 'Kantara: Chapter 1' also feature among his favorites for the year.

description: Never lose your car again! Google Maps offers a simple, hidden feature to save your parking spot. On Android, tap your location dot and select 'Save'. For iPhones, tap the blue dot and choose 'Saved parking'. The app guides you back, saving you precious time and frustration. This handy tool is a daily driver's best friend.

author: TNN
description: Two sisters in Lucknow died by suicide after allegedly being distraught over their pet dog's deteriorating health. The women, aged 22 and 24, reportedly consumed poison. description: Tragedy struck near the University of Toronto Scarborough campus as 20-year-old Indian-origin PhD student Shivank Avasthi was fatally shot on December 23, 2025. Toronto Police confirmed the incident as a homicide, with investigations ongoing and no motive yet established. The Indian Embassy expressed deep anguish, offering assistance to the bereaved family and highlighting concerns for international student safety.

description: A man, Pintu Barnwal, from Gopalganj district, Bihar, was arrested on charges of allegedly marrying three women over a span of three years, without divorcing any of his previous wives. The arrest followed complaints from his first and second wives, who accused him of domestic violence and demanding dowry.

description: Investors are beginning to penalize companies for layoffs, even those framed as AI-driven efficiency. Goldman Sachs analysts report a shift where stock prices decline following such announcements, suggesting skepticism about "AI restructuring" as a cover for declining profitability. Despite this market sentiment, layoffs are still predicted to rise as firms pursue AI for cost reduction.

description: Apple's highly anticipated foldable iPhone is reportedly set to launch next year, with leaked renders revealing a book-style design similar to Google's Pixel Fold. description: Gold, silver, and platinum have shattered previous records, reaching unprecedented highs. This surge is fueled by strong speculative interest, anticipated US interest rate cuts, and escalating geopolitical tensions. Silver notably surpassed $75 per ounce, with both precious and industrial metals experiencing significant gains amid global economic and political uncertainty.

Sooryavanshi's achievement marks a significant milestone early in his promising career.

The incident has raised serious questions about online accountability and real-world danger.

description: Hindus in Bangladesh are pleading with India to open its borders, fearing escalating violence and persecution following recent lynchings. description: Police are investigating the murder of a Union Bank assistant manager, Bhuvaneshwari, allegedly by her husband, Balamurugan. description: Ranveer Singh's 'Dhurandhar' shows no signs of slowing down, smashing records in its third week at the box office. description: A disturbing episode occurred near a workplace in Gurgaon, where a woman was shot by a man she had previously rebuffed. The police swiftly acted, arresting two suspects, Tushar and Shubham, in Uttar Pradesh. Tushar reportedly confessed that his violent outburst stemmed from his inability to accept her refusal, marking a troubling escalation of previous unwanted advances.

description: On Thursday night, the celebration at Mysuru Palace was shattered by the tragic explosion of a helium cylinder, resulting in one death and injuring four others, including visiting tourists. The sound of the blast carried a kilometer away, alarming the community as emergency crews rushed to the scene.

description: The government has directed the Survey of India to map the Aravalis using a new 100-meter height definition, sparking widespread protests. Environmentalists fear this shift to a height-based marker will significantly shrink the recognized ranges, potentially undermining conservation efforts for the predominantly low-lying Aravalis. The ministry maintains mining controls remain intact.

description: Fourteen-year-old Vaibhav Sooryavanshi made history by smashing 190 off 84 balls for Bihar against Arunachal Pradesh in the Vijay Hazare Trophy. He became the youngest to score a List A hundred and the first men’s cricketer to hit centuries in both List A and T20 cricket before 15. His knock helped Bihar post a record 574.

description: A viral video shows Braden “Clavicular” and N3on being splashed with a red liquid by a man many online users link to a past livestream crash. Social media reactions remain divided. An Adin Ross associate confirmed the man survived. Clavicular has stayed silent, and his Kick channel status remains unclear.

author: DEBABRATA MOHAPATRA, U SUDHAKAR REDDY, HRUSIKESH MOHANTY
description: Maoist commander Ganesh Uike, also known as Paka Hanumanthu and carrying a Rs 1.1 crore bounty, was killed in a security operation in Odisha's Kandhamal district. A central committee member and Odisha in-charge, he was linked to major operations like the 2013 Jhiram Ghati ambush. His death is considered a significant milestone in eliminating Naxalism.

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: US President Donald Trump announced a "powerful and deadly strike" against ISIS terrorists in northwest Nigeria, citing their targeting and killing of Christians. He claimed the "Department of War" executed "perfect strikes" at his direction, vowing to prevent radical Islamic terrorism from prospering. Trump had previously warned of repercussions if the slaughter of Christians continued.

author: ISHA JAIN
description: Uttar Pradesh schools will now make newspaper reading compulsory for students. A 10-minute slot during morning assembly will be dedicated to reading news, aiming to boost general knowledge, improve vocabulary, and foster critical thinking. This initiative seeks to reduce screen time and cultivate informed, empathetic citizens aware of local and global events.

author: PANKAJ SHAH AND VIVEK SINGH CHAUHAN
description: Prime Minister Modi, inaugurating a memorial in Lucknow, criticized past governments for glorifying a single family and neglecting national heroes. He stated the BJP government is rectifying this by honoring all contributors and dismantling barriers like Article 370. The memorial celebrates Jan Sangh stalwarts, emphasizing the BJP's commitment to merit-based recognition over dynastic politics.

description: Kobe Bryant and his teenage daughter, Vanessa Bryant, died in a tragic crash in 2020. Despite the tragedy, Vanessa Bryant has been able to rebuild her life along with their three daughters. Amid the mess, Kobe Bryant's wife, Vanessa Bryant, is now facing a tragic issue related to the NBA legend's legacy that he has left behind.

description: Urijah Faber believes Ilia Topuria has the best chance to become the UFC’s first triple champion. Speaking on December 24, Faber praised Topuria’s power and mindset. While Alex Pereira and Khamzat Chimaev are also in the mix, Topuria’s comments about Islam Makhachev keep his title dreams alive.
